WEBVTT

00:21.188 --> 00:22.678
In the 20th century,

00:23.148 --> 00:25.981
if you wanted to know your neighbors,
you move to the suburbs.

00:26.527 --> 00:29.895
If you wanted to become an addict,
you move to New York.

00:30.989 --> 00:34.607
Now, everything's upside down,
the junkies are in the burbs.

00:34.910 --> 00:37.868
And the building next door
is a fucking kickball league.

00:38.664 --> 00:41.702
It was an' against commerce
and commerce won.

00:42.626 --> 00:45.618
The kids think the only place
to find art is in the gallery.

00:45.796 --> 00:49.755
And the only place to find romance
is to confessing your love in the rain.

00:50.217 --> 00:51.378
Like in the movies.

00:51.843 --> 00:56.087
But it's messier than that.
There's always mess.

00:57.349 --> 01:00.592
It's safe here now,
but there's still urban decay.

01:01.144 --> 01:05.229
It's just, migrated to the dinner parties
of the upper Westside.

01:06.191 --> 01:09.104
The best lack all conviction
while the worst

01:09.236 --> 01:11.603
are filled with passionate intensity.

01:12.364 --> 01:17.279
Yeats said that but so did Lou Reed
Quoting him live at the Bottom Line.

01:18.662 --> 01:22.200
Lou Reed's gone and so is the Bottom Line.

01:22.666 --> 01:27.285
It's probably a Soul Cycle,
only soul the city has left.

01:28.880 --> 01:32.839
Everyone's pretending it's all okay.
But that's a lie.

01:33.635 --> 01:35.626
Something's missing and we all feel it.

01:36.555 --> 01:40.594
Including Thomas Webb,
he thought he had the answer.

01:41.351 --> 01:42.933
And her name was Mimi.

01:45.105 --> 01:48.894
Nineteen seventy-six. The city
was dirty, crime-ridden, and broke.

01:50.360 --> 01:52.067
It was the center
of the creative universe.

01:53.196 --> 01:54.402
New York's lost its soul.

01:55.073 --> 01:57.189
Most favorite neighborhood
at the moment is Philadelphia.

02:00.912 --> 02:02.198
- I like that.
- Yeah?

02:02.331 --> 02:05.449
- Yeah, where'd you lift that from?
- I didn't, it's mine.

02:06.543 --> 02:07.578
Well, it's good.

02:08.836 --> 02:10.828
So, will you come with me tonight?

02:11.965 --> 02:15.333
No, your mum's last dinner party
made me feel invisible.

02:15.469 --> 02:17.756
I know, but, we're invisible together.

02:18.180 --> 02:21.389
- If you don't like it, then you don't go.
- I have to go.

02:21.558 --> 02:23.674
My mother's unstable,
throwing dinner parties

02:23.769 --> 02:26.602
- is how she medicates.
- Yeah, what about the lithium and Xanax?

02:26.938 --> 02:29.726
Not to mention, the nicotine and Shiraz.

02:30.692 --> 02:31.682
Semantics.

02:35.280 --> 02:37.487
- I have to tell you something.
- Yeah?

02:37.783 --> 02:40.275
Yeah, I...

02:41.370 --> 02:46.115
- Might be going to Zagreb.
- Where?

02:46.750 --> 02:48.741
Zagreb, it's in Croatia.

02:50.045 --> 02:52.252
So, Helmut Graph,
he runs a workshop there.

02:52.798 --> 02:55.586
And I found out that
I can transfer my credits to NYU.

02:56.885 --> 03:02.551
That's... That's... terrible.

03:04.685 --> 03:05.675
Why?

03:07.145 --> 03:08.260
No, why is that terrible?

03:08.563 --> 03:10.520
Because you're the only thing
in my life I'm settled on.

03:11.108 --> 03:12.564
Thomas, what do you think is happening?

03:13.276 --> 03:15.483
Between me and you,
what do you think this is?

03:15.612 --> 03:19.901
- August 8th, I think August 8th was real.
- It was amazing.

03:21.034 --> 03:22.195
But it was just one night.

03:23.286 --> 03:26.824
I mean Nick was playing L.A.,
I was vulnerable.

03:27.416 --> 03:31.330
We were both on molly,
I thought I was a pirate.

03:35.382 --> 03:36.463
It was just one night.

03:38.719 --> 03:39.800
Well, I'm crazy about you.

03:40.804 --> 03:43.592
- And I'm crazy about you but...
- But, don't say as friends.

03:43.724 --> 03:47.058
- Why? Why is that so bad?
- Because pretty girls like to recruit

03:47.144 --> 03:48.634
their rejections and call them friends.

03:51.857 --> 03:52.938
Wow.

04:18.175 --> 04:21.668
For Mimi,
Thomas was like the new New York.

04:22.679 --> 04:25.011
No danger, no deliverance.

04:25.849 --> 04:29.433
It made him nurturing
and too boring to fall in love with.

04:30.437 --> 04:33.145
Mimi felt Thomas
was a boy without mystery.

04:34.316 --> 04:35.647
Thomas agreed.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.438
But all that was about to change.

05:02.803 --> 05:07.388
- Anything worth opening?
- Just bills and junk.

05:10.644 --> 05:16.560
W.F., W.F. Gerald I just moved into 2B.

05:17.818 --> 05:18.853
Thomas Webb.

05:20.821 --> 05:23.233
- Why so troubled, Thomas?
- Excuse me.

05:24.157 --> 05:26.148
I know that color of stress.

05:26.535 --> 05:31.325
It's much brighter than job issues,
more subdued than possible disease.

05:33.458 --> 05:36.120
- Sorry, I'm being rude.
- No, I mean...

05:38.296 --> 05:39.331
I'm having a bad day.

05:41.341 --> 05:42.376
What's her name?

05:46.137 --> 05:48.799
- It's Mimi.
- Mimi.

05:49.391 --> 05:53.055
Derived from Wilhelmina,
It means resolute protector.

05:55.438 --> 05:56.428
There you go.

05:57.816 --> 06:01.605
What a...
what is it you like about this Mimi?

06:03.071 --> 06:04.152
You're a psychiatrist?

06:05.031 --> 06:07.318
- No.
- You ask psychiatrist questions.

06:07.826 --> 06:08.941
Maybe I can help.

06:09.411 --> 06:12.449
Maybe I can help you
to get Mimi to sleep with you.

06:15.125 --> 06:16.581
How do you know, she hasn't already?

06:30.432 --> 06:31.718
It was nice meeting you.

06:34.227 --> 06:37.219
Well, why don't you let a new
neighbor help you out?

06:40.901 --> 06:42.357
What do you like about Mimi?

06:46.740 --> 06:48.322
I'm in 2B.

07:22.817 --> 07:24.023
Where'd you meet her?

07:24.653 --> 07:27.771
There's this book store
called The Pale Fire.

07:28.782 --> 07:32.446
- It's named after John Shade...
- John Shade's 999 line poem.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.159
Nabokov.

07:35.121 --> 07:36.156
Right, well.

07:37.082 --> 07:38.572
They sold rare, vintage books in there.

07:38.708 --> 07:40.619
And I'm into that.
Just reading off the beaten back and...

07:41.294 --> 07:44.252
Mimi works there,
she gave me the greatest recommendations.

07:45.382 --> 07:46.417
You know.

07:46.841 --> 07:49.082
She's putting herself
through NYU's writing program.

07:49.344 --> 07:52.052
- She reads a book a week.
- She's polishing her brain.

07:54.265 --> 07:55.346
Beautiful?

07:57.060 --> 07:58.141
Incredibly beautiful.

07:59.813 --> 08:01.770
Like she's direct from God, you know.

08:02.232 --> 08:04.143
On second generation,
if that makes sense.

08:04.401 --> 08:05.732
Don't believe sense.

08:06.653 --> 08:07.859
You know we get each other.

08:10.281 --> 08:11.646
Problem, was...

08:13.535 --> 08:16.243
ls, that she has this boyfriend.

08:17.414 --> 08:18.904
Nick, he's in that...

08:19.582 --> 08:21.448
band, Fahrenheit 185.

08:21.543 --> 08:24.080
The exact temperature
it takes to cook heroin.

08:26.589 --> 08:27.670
Properly.

08:32.429 --> 08:33.760
Let's see what we got.

08:40.562 --> 08:41.847
Here we go.

08:44.232 --> 08:46.690
Anyways, so, Nick goes on tour.

08:47.652 --> 08:50.144
Mimi's now available
and we're hanging out more.

08:51.656 --> 08:52.862
We end up spending...

08:54.034 --> 08:55.274
a magical night together.

08:56.453 --> 08:59.445
August 8th, and then...

09:01.583 --> 09:04.291
Nothing. All goes platonic.

09:06.087 --> 09:07.327
How old is Mimi?

09:07.672 --> 09:09.913
She's, 22. She just turned 22.

09:10.592 --> 09:11.753
She's young. Well...

09:12.802 --> 09:17.467
she's at an age,
where defense mechanisms are very strong.

09:17.766 --> 09:20.804
Despite her outer veneer,
she's ruled by fear.

09:21.519 --> 09:25.683
Like so many of us at that time.
I know... what you need to do.

09:26.941 --> 09:31.481
Just make her afraid of something more
than being with you, in that way.

09:32.655 --> 09:33.645
Which is?

09:36.326 --> 09:37.441
Not being with you.

09:39.746 --> 09:40.781
But how?

09:41.581 --> 09:42.742
How I am supposed to do that?

09:44.334 --> 09:46.291
Let life take over,

09:48.797 --> 09:51.209
find a window and pounce.

09:54.302 --> 09:57.135
That's it?
That's you sage-ably advice?

09:58.932 --> 10:00.843
- Can I have my money back, please?
- Thomas.

10:01.392 --> 10:03.554
- Is it Thomas or Tom?
- It's Thomas.

10:03.978 --> 10:05.889
- Not Tommy?
- No, never.

10:06.397 --> 10:09.480
Thomas, you're not giving life
enough credit.

10:09.609 --> 10:11.771
The unpredictable forces of humanity...

10:12.153 --> 10:15.942
My life is not unpredictable,
my life is conventional my life is boring.

10:16.366 --> 10:19.529
No, it's as random as it is deliberate.

10:22.413 --> 10:24.074
It's funny as it is tragic.

10:26.334 --> 10:28.951
Yours is no exception. I gotta piss.

10:36.553 --> 10:38.965
Dinner parties
were Judith's safety blanket.

10:39.055 --> 10:42.138
A table full of artists
took her mind of her herself.

10:42.433 --> 10:46.768
The swirl of distractions,
seating plans, gossip, food,

10:47.063 --> 10:48.929
anything to keep away the dread.

10:49.858 --> 10:52.725
They were the perfect antidote
to her childhood dinners.

10:53.111 --> 10:55.398
The silences, the drunken outbursts.

10:55.864 --> 10:59.107
Artists came to New York from all over,
and she always took them in.

10:59.325 --> 11:02.693
Clinging to the illusion
of an open happy family.

11:03.079 --> 11:05.696
Do you miss getting mugged
on Central Park West...

11:05.790 --> 11:08.407
- Exactly, exactly.
- No, but I do miss,

11:08.751 --> 11:11.869
the second avenue deli,
I miss the Lenox Lounge.

11:12.005 --> 11:15.248
I mean do you know,
what are in those iconic places now.

11:15.550 --> 11:17.541
Urban Outfitters, a Starbucks.

11:17.719 --> 11:20.461
There's a John Varvatos
where CBGB's use to be.

11:21.139 --> 11:22.925
- New York's lost its soul.
- Exactly!

11:24.475 --> 11:25.556
What was that Thomas?

11:26.978 --> 11:30.767
Well, I was just agreeing with David
that New York has lost its soul.

11:31.316 --> 11:34.775
Since he returned from 3 months in Peru,
he's decided to hate where he's from.

11:34.903 --> 11:35.938
No, it's true.

11:36.279 --> 11:38.896
New York's most vibrant neighborhood
at the moment is Philadelphia.

11:42.285 --> 11:43.696
That's very funny, Thomas.

11:44.495 --> 11:47.283
So, Ethan. I heard you've commissioned
Nick Bilton

11:47.415 --> 11:49.031
to write the biography on Evan Dereif.

11:49.250 --> 11:53.164
Our mandate, it came to us very simple.
Bios on any haircut under 40,

11:53.296 --> 11:55.458
as long as they're still
within their fifteen minutes.

11:55.882 --> 11:57.543
Self-help, political rants.

11:58.009 --> 12:00.626
- Nobody reads fiction anymore.
- Anyone's a writer...

12:01.346 --> 12:03.758
- so cynical, Ethan Webb.
- I know...

12:04.140 --> 12:05.972
If I were a writer,

12:06.059 --> 12:08.767
we'd be having this conversation
in a two bedroom in Bushwick.

12:09.062 --> 12:10.848
Bushwick is expensive now.

12:11.856 --> 12:14.814
I'm serious, I'm really serious,
I mean, most novelists these days,

12:15.568 --> 12:17.559
they don't own enough money
to support themselves.

12:17.820 --> 12:19.356
No matter how talented they are.

12:19.656 --> 12:22.318
That's why if Thomas came to me
with a desire to be writer.

12:24.744 --> 12:25.779
I'd talk him out of it.

12:27.747 --> 12:30.114
So, you're still tutoring, right?

12:31.084 --> 12:32.666
Yeah, just for some extra cash.

12:32.835 --> 12:34.792
- He could be a Spanish teacher.
- Yes, he actually could.

12:35.004 --> 12:37.962
- I don't know if I could be a Spanish...
- If you went back to collage for a year.

12:38.216 --> 12:39.877
For some reason he refuses to do it.

12:40.260 --> 12:42.422
He lives on the lower east side
without any direction.

12:43.346 --> 12:45.087
Only thing missing is an opium habit.

12:45.974 --> 12:47.885
What about doing a smartphone application?

13:29.058 --> 13:30.890
This man moved in
across the hall from me.

13:31.144 --> 13:32.930
I don't what he does, or who he is but,

13:33.813 --> 13:35.178
Seems familiar to me.

13:35.606 --> 13:36.641
He's my new friend.

13:36.941 --> 13:38.022
Yeah.

13:38.860 --> 13:41.727
- He asked about you.
- Me? He knows me.

13:49.787 --> 13:50.902
What's my father doing here?

13:55.585 --> 13:56.700
Who's he with?

13:58.588 --> 13:59.703
I don't know.

14:01.716 --> 14:02.831
She's beautiful.

14:32.830 --> 14:34.992
Do you have any idea
what this is gonna do to my mother?

14:37.627 --> 14:40.210
This doesn't mean
your father loves you any less.

14:43.841 --> 14:45.457
I'm sorry, that was bad enough.

14:46.386 --> 14:49.048
I know like dispensing therapy
from an after-school specialist...

14:49.180 --> 14:51.467
He doesn't care about me
to begin with I know that.

14:53.059 --> 14:56.222
This... this is about my mother.

14:57.063 --> 14:59.100
Yeah, but, it's their problem.

14:59.440 --> 15:01.181
- You have your own problems.
- Like what?

15:02.276 --> 15:05.439
Actually don't, don't answer that.
Not now.

15:08.032 --> 15:11.024
Thomas, look at me.

15:12.662 --> 15:14.653
Look, your parents,

15:15.456 --> 15:16.491
their world,

15:17.250 --> 15:18.866
is nothing like ours.

15:21.712 --> 15:23.623
I mean maybe it's their generation or...

15:25.758 --> 15:27.294
I don't know this island.

15:30.304 --> 15:31.419
But you're kind.

15:32.849 --> 15:34.135
And you're real.

15:50.283 --> 15:51.398
Don't do that.

15:59.876 --> 16:02.368
Mimi, look, you're young,

16:03.129 --> 16:05.791
and your defense mechanism is strong,
but I think that you want this.

16:07.133 --> 16:10.967
- I think that you're confused right now.
- No Mimi, I'm angry right now.

16:12.180 --> 16:13.170
I'm angry.

16:14.640 --> 16:16.847
Did you see that woman?
Did you see how beautiful she was?

16:18.478 --> 16:19.889
I could never get a woman like that.

16:20.646 --> 16:25.231
My father with his publishing house,
his good looks, and it's cheating...

16:26.152 --> 16:27.187
fucking hair.

16:27.737 --> 16:29.068
So what, you're gonna use

16:30.156 --> 16:33.490
your father's affairs as a confirmation
of your own inadequacies?

16:36.704 --> 16:37.785
No, I mean.

16:40.416 --> 16:41.497
I have you for that.

16:45.421 --> 16:47.412
So, you call my office,

16:47.798 --> 16:50.130
you say you wanna have lunch,
you never wanna have lunch.

16:51.344 --> 16:52.834
I figured you had a big surprise.

16:53.304 --> 16:55.215
- Maybe you figured out your life.
- No.

16:55.765 --> 16:57.130
Definitely haven't figured out my life.

16:58.476 --> 17:00.467
- I wanted to speak to you about...
- Ethan.

17:00.728 --> 17:02.560
- Good to see you.
- Of course anytime.

17:02.730 --> 17:04.641
- I actually enjoyed the show.
- It was good, wasn't it?

17:04.732 --> 17:06.314
- It was great.
- Great, say hi to Judith.

17:06.483 --> 17:07.973
I will indeed.

17:10.154 --> 17:12.020
I want you to move
from the lower east side.

17:13.115 --> 17:16.824
Why do you insist on living in the
farthest corner of Manhattan away from us?

17:17.244 --> 17:18.326
I think it's intentional.

17:19.454 --> 17:22.071
I think it's almost hurtful.

17:24.042 --> 17:25.032
Look.

17:26.337 --> 17:29.125
I'm not asking for me,
I'm asking for your mother.

17:30.591 --> 17:31.877
She wants you closer to home.

17:33.261 --> 17:34.296
How is mom?

17:36.013 --> 17:37.003
Better.

17:38.891 --> 17:39.881
I guess.

17:43.229 --> 17:45.345
- Can't get her to quit smoking.
- She is fragile.

17:46.232 --> 17:49.395
Anything, even the smallest thing could,
create another,

17:50.570 --> 17:51.605
incident.

17:59.161 --> 18:00.492
I'll pay the difference in rent.

18:05.960 --> 18:07.075
Will you think about it?

18:07.962 --> 18:09.498
- Dad.
- Also, I setup an appointment

18:09.630 --> 18:12.748
with a career counselor for you.
My office will email you the info.

18:13.009 --> 18:15.467
Dad, I know you, I know...

18:15.970 --> 18:17.426
You know I'm what, Thomas?

18:20.349 --> 18:21.464
I know you're just trying to help.

18:22.643 --> 18:23.849
Don't blow it up, okay?

18:24.312 --> 18:26.223
I had to call in a favor for her
to see you,

18:26.355 --> 18:27.470
she actually has a waiting list.

18:30.484 --> 18:34.569
- Are you gonna confront your father?
- No, trouble talking to him.

18:35.573 --> 18:36.563
Why?

18:37.617 --> 18:38.948
I don't think, he likes me that much.

18:41.162 --> 18:42.197
What the...

18:44.248 --> 18:46.285
What exactly is wrong with your mother?

18:48.002 --> 18:50.334
I don't know, she's depressed. Bipolar.

18:50.880 --> 18:52.291
She's depressive bipolar.

18:54.050 --> 18:55.836
She came from a broken home, so.

18:57.219 --> 18:59.335
Whenever anything threatens
our perfect family,

18:59.472 --> 19:01.338
she, completely unravels.

19:04.852 --> 19:06.889
Can't tell her, she'd be destroyed.

19:09.982 --> 19:11.222
Why don't you furnished this place?

19:12.360 --> 19:13.771
I live in Brooklyn.

19:16.989 --> 19:19.105
- You have two apartments?
- I'm rich.

19:20.159 --> 19:21.445
I'm a fucking duke.

19:30.419 --> 19:33.377
Maybe he's,
been faithful all these years.

19:34.423 --> 19:36.664
Maybe she came on to him,
I've seen her, she's irresistible.

19:36.842 --> 19:38.128
- I mean...
- Alright, stop.

19:41.055 --> 19:43.888
- What do you want?
- Well, my father stop seeing this woman.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.015
No, no, no, in life?

19:47.687 --> 19:48.802
You know, in your life.

19:51.190 --> 19:53.477
You want more money?
You want more respect?

19:56.404 --> 19:57.735
What is that you want?

19:59.782 --> 20:02.319
Think about it, really think about it.

20:04.829 --> 20:06.866
- I wanna be better.
- Better?

20:08.332 --> 20:09.322
In what?

20:16.006 --> 20:16.996
I don't know.

20:19.427 --> 20:23.261
In the 80's, Ethan was intoxicated
by literary New York.

20:23.931 --> 20:27.925
But when he accepted that he lacked
the talent to create a fictional family,

20:28.018 --> 20:30.680
he thought, at least he could create
a real one.

20:31.063 --> 20:32.804
Young Thomas loved to write.

20:33.149 --> 20:34.514
Ethan ignored this.

20:35.067 --> 20:39.061
Wary of nurturing a life of rejections
and evictions.

20:39.363 --> 20:41.946
And Thomas learned
to keep his stories to himself.

20:42.783 --> 20:45.320
The intensity of Judith's bond
with her son,

20:45.411 --> 20:48.324
left Ethan feeling like a stranger
in his own home.

20:49.623 --> 20:54.038
He sought refuge in work,
until publishing began its slow decline.

20:55.087 --> 20:57.419
Then came Johanna.

20:58.799 --> 21:00.961
You know, private detectives
get paid by the hour.

21:02.011 --> 21:03.467
To just, just wait.

21:04.263 --> 21:07.255
To do exactly what we're doing right now.
What is the difficulty in a stakeout?

21:11.479 --> 21:12.514
I really gotta go to class.

21:12.772 --> 21:14.809
No, just wait, all right?
He's gonna be out in a minute.

21:16.984 --> 21:18.600
I have to see
if he's gonna meet her again.

21:19.487 --> 21:20.568
Please.

21:21.489 --> 21:22.524
Just wait.

21:25.117 --> 21:26.198
Okay.

21:31.332 --> 21:32.367
My God, that's her.

21:33.417 --> 21:34.452
The other woman.

21:36.754 --> 21:37.835
I'll call you later.

21:37.963 --> 21:40.204
- Wait, aren't we waiting for your dad.
- I'll call you later.

23:23.319 --> 23:26.778
What is it exactly
that you wanna accomplish?

23:28.282 --> 23:29.397
I wanna meet her.

23:30.284 --> 23:31.774
I wanna tell her to stop seeing my father.

23:32.870 --> 23:35.362
- She could kill my mother.
- So, do it.

23:38.417 --> 23:39.703
I haven't built up the courage yet.

23:42.880 --> 23:45.872
- So you stalk her.
- I shouldn't be dealing with this at all.

23:46.967 --> 23:48.378
I should be on a beach,

23:49.428 --> 23:50.418
With Mimi.

