42:53.321 --> 42:54.436
I think about her...

42:57.742 --> 42:58.732
all the time.

43:03.331 --> 43:04.321
Maybe it's love.

43:08.544 --> 43:09.579
I don't know.

43:10.588 --> 43:12.249
Love is hard to determine.

43:12.507 --> 43:15.841
People think they're in love
and it's something completely different.

43:16.844 --> 43:18.334
Infatuation.

43:19.722 --> 43:21.633
The righting of childhood wrongs.

43:22.100 --> 43:23.340
No companionship.

43:26.104 --> 43:27.139
Have you ever been in love?

43:27.855 --> 43:29.016
Yeah, once.

43:31.359 --> 43:32.440
Who was she?

43:35.404 --> 43:37.020
She was this woman I knew.

43:38.783 --> 43:41.195
She was taken by someone else,
a dear friend.

43:44.205 --> 43:46.867
We had a profound connection,
but she was his girl.

43:47.208 --> 43:48.198
It was a mess.

43:49.377 --> 43:50.412
So what did you do?

43:50.920 --> 43:52.877
I left the scene of the crime.

43:54.340 --> 43:55.421
You ran away?

43:56.384 --> 43:59.752
Well, at the time
I called it an adventure.

44:00.513 --> 44:02.800
But hindsight turned
it into something else

44:02.932 --> 44:05.344
which is what hindsight inevitably does.

44:06.310 --> 44:08.722
Yeah, I ran away.
I'm gonna take this.

44:09.647 --> 44:11.888
- Leave you with your heart on.
- My hard on.

44:13.025 --> 44:14.936
Heart, your heart on.

44:15.778 --> 44:16.893
You know what, maybe,

44:17.029 --> 44:20.021
in hindsight I'll feel guilty
about Johanna, but right now I don't.

44:24.287 --> 44:25.322
It's not cut or dry.

44:26.247 --> 44:27.863
Congratulations, Thomas.

44:29.167 --> 44:31.204
Your world's becoming contextual.

44:36.883 --> 44:38.339
Who the fuck are you?

44:50.062 --> 44:51.143
Hey dad.

44:52.315 --> 44:53.350
What's up?

44:54.233 --> 44:55.268
Sit down.

45:00.448 --> 45:01.438
Is everything alright?

45:02.241 --> 45:03.322
Is mom okay?

45:04.285 --> 45:05.446
Sit down, Thomas.

45:19.425 --> 45:20.915
Is there anything you want
to tell me?

45:25.389 --> 45:26.424
No.

45:26.974 --> 45:28.009
No, nothing.

45:29.435 --> 45:30.550
Anything I should know?

45:35.441 --> 45:36.431
No.

45:38.611 --> 45:39.601
Thomas...

45:41.072 --> 45:43.359
You blew off the career counselor.

45:45.785 --> 45:48.026
I told you how hard it was
to get that appointment

45:48.120 --> 45:49.736
and then you just don't show up.

45:49.830 --> 45:51.036
- Gone!
- Right, I'm...

45:54.335 --> 45:56.918
- I should have called. Sorry.
- You should have called. I'm sorry.

45:57.129 --> 45:58.210
I'm sorry, too.

46:02.969 --> 46:04.084
Come work here.

46:05.012 --> 46:07.253
Work here. You like to read.

46:07.640 --> 46:09.631
I've been conflicted about
giving you a job here,

46:09.767 --> 46:11.758
nepotism and all that bullshit,
but screw it.

46:12.812 --> 46:15.930
You can start under the junior editors.
You know, learn something.

46:16.190 --> 46:17.271
- No, thank you.
- Why not?

46:17.692 --> 46:19.774
I mean what's wrong with
learning the publishing business?

46:19.860 --> 46:21.601
Nothing. It's fine.
It's just it's...

46:23.823 --> 46:24.813
Serviceable.

46:35.668 --> 46:36.703
W.F.?

46:38.921 --> 46:40.207
I just wanna get my essays back.

46:41.549 --> 46:42.630
Hey.

47:44.278 --> 47:45.313
Thomas.

47:45.780 --> 47:46.941
I was in your apartment.

47:51.118 --> 47:52.199
You're Julian Stellars.

47:54.789 --> 47:56.029
A nom de plume.

47:56.874 --> 47:58.285
You've had twelve books published.

47:59.794 --> 48:02.286
You don't have much mass appeal,
but you don't seem to mind.

48:03.506 --> 48:05.247
Hard to find a picture of you anywhere.

48:06.592 --> 48:09.175
You're an alcoholic who spends
most afternoons drinking

48:09.345 --> 48:10.460
in Brooklyn Inn.

48:10.888 --> 48:13.300
And you're probably the only person
I've met that's actually,

48:14.016 --> 48:15.723
actually been to an opium den.

48:17.812 --> 48:19.143
Have I been googled?

48:25.444 --> 48:26.525
I didn't read it.

48:28.572 --> 48:29.607
The new manuscript.

48:33.369 --> 48:35.485
Well, Thomas, I appreciate that.

48:42.628 --> 48:43.663
So...

48:46.757 --> 48:47.872
You said I had talent.

48:49.552 --> 48:51.463
It was a professional's opinion.

48:55.307 --> 48:57.173
I don't know, man. I...

48:58.686 --> 49:01.428
You've experienced the world.
I just live here in New York.

49:02.398 --> 49:03.809
New York is the world.

49:04.024 --> 49:05.480
I haven't done much with my life.

49:09.572 --> 49:12.109
You've had sex
with your father's mistress?

49:14.076 --> 49:15.441
I'd say that's something.

49:18.289 --> 49:19.871
Am I the only living boy in New York?

49:26.130 --> 49:27.165
You are.

49:46.317 --> 49:47.978
Hey. I was outside your apartment.

49:48.611 --> 49:52.275
You're not there, I brought the essays.
I wanted to show you.

50:32.780 --> 50:33.861
Did you sleep with her?

50:38.994 --> 50:39.984
With who?

50:44.291 --> 50:45.497
Johanna?

50:47.086 --> 50:48.201
Why would you ask that?

50:49.922 --> 50:51.708
They left the wedding
as quickly as we did.

50:53.884 --> 50:55.625
I may be oblivious but I am not stupid.

50:56.428 --> 50:57.884
- Why do you care?
- I just do.

50:58.013 --> 50:59.174
- Why?
- Thomas.

51:00.474 --> 51:01.930
- You jealous?
- No.

51:02.393 --> 51:03.508
- You sure?
- Thomas.

51:04.186 --> 51:05.176
I think you are jealous.

51:05.271 --> 51:07.353
- Did you sleep with her?
- She's my father's mistress.

51:09.275 --> 51:10.436
You think that I would do that?

51:13.487 --> 51:14.568
No.

51:16.073 --> 51:17.108
Thank you.

51:19.159 --> 51:20.194
You're sweet.

51:21.328 --> 51:22.443
You're not like them.

51:23.289 --> 51:25.121
- Like who?
- The city.

51:34.383 --> 51:35.748
I want you to stop seeing him.

51:38.304 --> 51:39.544
No, I'm putting my foot down.

51:40.222 --> 51:41.929
