to do, Thomas.

51:42.057 --> 51:44.924
- I don't care if your foot's down or up.
- Why, cause you don't care about anything?

51:45.227 --> 51:46.433
- What?
- You obviously don't

51:46.604 --> 51:47.810
care about anything at all.

51:48.564 --> 51:50.100
So, I'm a nihilist now, am I?

51:54.653 --> 51:55.768
I don't know anything about you.

51:58.574 --> 51:59.564
Where did you grow up?

52:00.451 --> 52:02.362
Brooklyn, Thomas.
That's why I have this accent.

52:05.331 --> 52:06.446
Did you play sports?

52:07.291 --> 52:08.281
No.

52:10.794 --> 52:12.034
When did you first have sex?

52:12.921 --> 52:15.504
My God,
are we gonna talk about my childhood now?

52:15.841 --> 52:17.127
Yeah, I wanna know you.

52:18.886 --> 52:20.047
Where did you grow up?

52:21.972 --> 52:23.633
I grew up in London.

52:24.391 --> 52:25.472
Which part?

52:26.477 --> 52:27.558
Belsize Park.

52:29.355 --> 52:31.096
Then, Kilburn.

52:31.398 --> 52:32.479
Why the move?

52:33.609 --> 52:36.021
Because Kilburn is so much more real.

52:37.363 --> 52:38.398
What your dad do?

52:42.076 --> 52:43.237
What does your dad do?

52:43.494 --> 52:47.032
He put a gun in his
mouth and pulled the trigger.

52:57.966 --> 52:59.047
I'm sorry.

53:04.932 --> 53:05.967
I didn't know.

53:11.021 --> 53:12.136
Why do you sleep with me?

53:13.774 --> 53:16.357
- Because I like you.
- What do you like about me?

53:18.904 --> 53:19.985
Your innocence.

53:21.115 --> 53:22.196
Were you ever innocent?

53:24.201 --> 53:25.191
I forgot.

53:25.703 --> 53:26.784
Come on? Tell me.

53:28.706 --> 53:30.367
I wanna know about when you were innocent.

53:30.624 --> 53:32.456
- Why?
- Because I like the idea of it.

53:33.544 --> 53:35.535
If you want someone so pure,
why are you with me?

53:36.130 --> 53:37.211
Because I care about you.

53:42.219 --> 53:43.334
You care about me?

53:46.056 --> 53:47.672
I don't care for anyone, remember?

53:50.769 --> 53:53.978
But the truth was,
she cared about them both.

53:55.315 --> 53:58.433
And that's when she knew,
this mess would only get worse.

53:59.486 --> 54:02.478
She had to make a clean break,
starting with Ethan.

54:03.991 --> 54:08.531
What she didn't anticipate was,
he'd surrendered too much of his past

54:08.996 --> 54:10.532
to give up on his future.

54:20.591 --> 54:22.207
You think he's in love with her?

54:23.469 --> 54:24.584
He just has to stop.

54:25.345 --> 54:26.506
You and your father...

54:27.347 --> 54:29.554
You suffer from the same disease.

54:30.225 --> 54:31.260
Johanna.

54:32.060 --> 54:35.143
Visions of Johanna.
Conquered my mind.

54:37.357 --> 54:38.438
Why are you writing about me?

54:42.029 --> 54:43.064
That's what I do.

54:43.530 --> 54:46.864
I write about people I know
and then give them a thin veil.

54:47.743 --> 54:48.778
Why me?

54:51.663 --> 54:52.653
Look, I...

54:53.874 --> 54:55.740
I got the apartment
to get out of the house

54:55.918 --> 54:57.955
and write a completely different story.

54:58.796 --> 55:01.083
- It didn't come across.
- Mine did.

55:02.716 --> 55:04.047
But like everything good,

55:04.468 --> 55:08.086
it happened by accident.
I met you, now I got 118 pages.

55:11.266 --> 55:14.258
My father's publishing house, they're
throwing an anniversary party tomorrow.

55:15.229 --> 55:16.219
You should come.

55:18.273 --> 55:19.388
